Kenya has recorded 236 new Covid-19 cases in the past 24 hours, raising the cumulative number to 95,431.
While releasing the figures Thursday afternoon, Health Cabinet Secretary Mutahi Kagwe said the new cases were reported from a sample of 3,773.
The cumulative tests in Kenya now stand at 1,025,653.
In the same period, four more patients succumbed to the disease, raising deaths from the virus in Kenya to 1,652.



